<h1>磅</h1><p class=neha><span style="color:#000099;">bàng</span><span class=alesi>(bang4)</span> , <span style="color:#cc7700;">páng</span><span class=alesi>(pang2)</span> , <span style="color:#990000;">pāng</span><span class=alesi>(pang1)</span> <span class=lesi>// pronunciations of 磅 in Mandarin Pinyin</span></p><h2>Basic information about 磅</h2><div class=abo>
<p><b>Unihan definition:</b> <a href="/dictionary/pound" style="color:black;">pound</a>; <a href="/dictionary/weigh" style="color:black;">weigh</a></p><p><b>Number of strokes:</b> 15<br><small>Examples of other characters consisting of 15 strokes: <a href="/character/题" title="ti2: forehead; title, headline; theme">题</a>, <a href="/character/德" title="de2: ethics, morality, virtue">德</a>, <a href="/character/影" title="ying3: shadow; image, reflection; photograph">影</a>, <a href="/character/增" title="zeng1: increase, add to, augment">增</a>, <a href="/character/靠" title="kao4: lean on, trust, depend on; near">靠</a>, <a href="/character/额" title="e2: forehead; tablet, plaque; fixed">额</a>, <a href="/character/镇" title="zhen4: town, market place; suppress">镇</a>, <a href="/character/篇" title="pian1: chapter, section, essay, article">篇</a>, <a href="/character/暴" title="bao4: violent, brutal, tyrannical">暴</a>, <a href="/character/熟" title="shu2: well-cooked; ripe; familiar with">熟</a></small></p><p><b>Radical:</b> <a href="/character/石" title="Kangxi radical 112">石</a>&nbsp;112.10</p><p><b>HSK level:</b> 6 <br><small>Other HSK 6 characters: <a href="/character/桨" title="jiang3: oar, paddle">桨</a>, <a href="/character/锤" title="chui2: balance weight on scale; hammer">锤</a>, <a href="/character/慷" title="kang1: ardent; generous, magnanimous">慷</a>, <a href="/character/馈" title="kui4: offer food superior; send gift">馈</a>, <a href="/character/溅" title="jian4: sprinkle, spray; spill, splash">溅</a>, <a href="/character/钙" title="gai4: calcium">钙</a>, <a href="/character/呻" title="shen1: groan, moan; recite with intonation">呻</a>, <a href="/character/彰" title="zhang1: clear, manifest, obvious">彰</a>, <a href="/character/眯" title="mi1: be blinded">眯</a>, <a href="/character/墟" title="xu1: high mound; hilly countryside; wasteland">墟</a> <a href="/character-list/hsk/level-6" title="List of HSK 6 characters" style="white-space: nowrap;">more hsk 6 charaters &raquo;</a></small></p